==Old English==
===Etymology===
A West Germanic word, of ultimately unknown origin.  Cognate with Middle Dutch [[haghetisse]] (Dutch [[heks]]), Old High German [[hazus]], [[hazussa]] (German [[Hexe]]).

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'hægtesse/

===Noun===
'''hægtesse''' ''f''
# a [[witch]], a [[Fury]]

